        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 1:29PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 128 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dolgeville, or near Little Falls, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oregon, Ingham Mills, Crum Creek, Garlock Corners, Curtis, Clockmill
Corners, Blackbridge, Lotville, Whitehouse, Rasbach Corner, Doxtater
Corner, Knappville, Shaker Place, Burrell Corners, Piseco, Shedd
Corners, Phipps Corners, Arietta, Ingham Mills Station, and Powley
Place.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
eastern New York.</instruction>
